# Static website — rebuild `dist/` before preview or verification

The `@umbraculum/website` workspace (and equivalent static brochure workspaces in sibling repos) is **build-only**: HTML/CSS live in `public/`; `scripts/build.mjs` copies them to gitignored `dist/`. Local preview (`npm run preview`), the compose `website` service (`serve dist`), and Cloudflare Pages all consume **`dist/`**, not `public/`.

## Rule (hard)

**Whenever** you edit files under `apps/website/public/**` (or change `apps/website/scripts/build.mjs`), you **must** refresh `dist/` **before**:

- opening or curling a local preview URL (e.g. `http://127.0.0.1:4321/support/`);
- declaring the edit done or passing public-endpoint verification on brochure pages;
- telling the user to refresh the browser and expect new content.

**Do not** assume the preview server watches `public/` — it does not.

## Refresh commands (pick one path)

**Docker Compose** (when the stack defines a `website` service):

```bash
docker compose restart website
```

**Host / workspace** (container-only npm per `00-shared-node-npm-container-only.mdc` when applicable):

```bash
npm run build -w @umbraculum/website
```

Then preview if needed: `npm run preview -w @umbraculum/website` (host) or rely on the restarted compose service.

## Symptom recognition

If source under `public/` shows the new copy but the browser at `:4321` still shows old text (e.g. "Donation channels are not wired yet"), **`dist/` is stale** — rebuild, not a caching bug in the product app.

## Frontier-now / local-subagent fit

- **Rule (this file):** always-on guardrail when glob matches; no runbook beyond the two refresh paths above.
- **Not a Skill:** procedure is two bounded commands; no troubleshooting tree warrants a separate skill.
- **Not a Subagent:** no delegation trigger; agents apply this inline after brochure edits.

